The article reports that Jose W. Fernandez from New York has been nominated for several positions. He has been nominated to be the United States Alternate Governor of the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development for a term of five years, as well as the United States Alternate Governor of the Inter-American Development Bank for a term of five years. He is also nominated to be the United States Alternate Governor of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development. Additionally, Fernandez has been nominated to be an Under Secretary of State for Economic Growth, Energy, and the Environment. These nominations are to replace Keith Krach in these positions.